title: James Webb Telescope Captures New Image of ‘Pillars of Creation’
description: The NASA space observatory’s infrared eye finds out what’s going on within the cloudy cosmic nursery.
dc:creator: Dennis Overbye
media:description: “Pillars of Creation” captured in NASA’s James Webb Space Telescope’s near-infrared view. The pillars resemble arches and spires rising from a desert, but are filled with semitransparent gas and dust.
